abstract: The Socialist Democrats' candidate Zoran Milanovic was leading in the first round of Croatia's presidential election, an exit poll on state television showed on Sunday.
snippet: The Socialist Democrats' candidate Zoran Milanovic was leading in the first round of Croatia's presidential election, an exit poll on state television showed on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: ZAGREB — The Socialist Democrats' candidate Zoran Milanovic was leading in the first round of Croatia's presidential election, an exit poll on state television showed on Sunday.
headline_main: Opposition Candidate Milanovic Leads in Croat Presidential Run: Exit Poll
headline_print_headline: Opposition Candidate Milanovic Leads in Croat Presidential Run: Exit Poll

abstract: Bolivia on Sunday announced its entry into the Lima Group regional bloc that was set up to find a way out of the Venezuelan crisis.
snippet: Bolivia on Sunday announced its entry into the Lima Group regional bloc that was set up to find a way out of the Venezuelan crisis.
lead_paragraph: La Paz (Reuters) - Bolivia on Sunday announced its entry into the Lima Group regional bloc that was set up to find a way out of the Venezuelan crisis.
headline_main: Bolivia Announces Entry Into Lima Group to Resolve Venezuelan Crisis
headline_print_headline: Bolivia Announces Entry Into Lima Group to Resolve Venezuelan Crisis

abstract: The authorities attributed the chain of crashes on Sunday morning to fog, ice and rubbernecking.
snippet: The authorities attributed the chain of crashes on Sunday morning to fog, ice and rubbernecking.
lead_paragraph: A pileup involving nearly 70 vehicles on an icy and foggy Virginia highway on Sunday morning left at least 51 people hurt, the police said.

abstract: A Cuban doctor waiting for asylum in the United States has become the only full-time physician at a makeshift encampment for 2,500 migrants in Mexico.
snippet: A Cuban doctor waiting for asylum in the United States has become the only full-time physician at a makeshift encampment for 2,500 migrants in Mexico.
lead_paragraph: MATAMOROS, Mexico — Under a canopy on the edge of a squalid encampment, a young physician named Dairon Elisondo Rojas holds office hours every day from 10 to 4.

abstract: Chelsea defender Antonio Rüdiger demanded swift punishments for Tottenham fans who aimed monkey noises at him on Sunday during a London derby where the stadium announcer issued three warnings for the racism to stop in an unprecedented move for the Premier League.

lead_paragraph: LONDON — Chelsea defender Antonio Rüdiger demanded swift punishments for Tottenham fans who aimed monkey noises at him on Sunday during a London derby where the stadium announcer issued three warnings for the racism to stop in an unprecedented move for the Premier League.

abstract: A body was found near a cabin in northwestern Michigan where a 47-year-old Detroit-area woman reportedly went missing in October, authorities said.

lead_paragraph: HONOR, Mich. — A body was found near a cabin in northwestern Michigan where a 47-year-old Detroit-area woman reportedly went missing in October, authorities said.

abstract: Despite a growing health crisis that has killed more than 50 people, vaping has become an irresistible — and addictive — part of life for many college students.
snippet: Despite a growing health crisis that has killed more than 50 people, vaping has become an irresistible — and addictive — part of life for many college students.
lead_paragraph: ATHENS, Ga. — Gail Moody had her first e-cigarette inhale of the day moments after waking up one recent morning. She took more puffs while showering. Aerosolized nicotine filled her lungs again during a break in her morning run, between mouthfuls of lunch, and as she worked at a tobacco shop near the University of Georgia, where she is a sophomore.

abstract: After an anthrax outbreak killed scores of people in 1979, she showed how even a tiny amount of a biological warfare agent could threaten a population.
snippet: After an anthrax outbreak killed scores of people in 1979, she showed how even a tiny amount of a biological warfare agent could threaten a population.
lead_paragraph: Jeanne Guillemin, an eminent medical anthropologist and scientific sleuth who helped expose a secret biological warfare lab in the Soviet Union as the source of a lethal anthrax outbreak, died on Nov. 15 at her home in Cambridge, Mass. She was 76.

abstract: The leaders of Cyprus, Greece and Israel plan to sign an agreement early in the new year for the building of the eastern Mediterranean natural gas pipeline, the Greek prime minister’s office announced Sunday.
snippet: The leaders of Cyprus, Greece and Israel plan to sign an agreement early in the new year for the building of the eastern Mediterranean natural gas pipeline, the Greek prime minister’s office announced Sunday.
lead_paragraph: ATHENS, Greece — The leaders of Cyprus, Greece and Israel plan to sign an agreement early in the new year for the building of the eastern Mediterranean natural gas pipeline, the Greek prime minister’s office announced Sunday.
headline_main: Cyprus, Greece, Israel to Sign Pipeline Deal on Jan. 2
headline_print_headline: Cyprus, Greece, Israel to Sign Pipeline Deal on Jan. 2
